Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Description: CLI launcher for certified MCP servers
 MCP is a command-line tool that resolves, downloads, validates, and executes
 MCP (Model Context Protocol) packages from the MCP Hub registry.
 .
 It enforces security policies, applies resource limits, and sandboxes
 processes with platform-specific isolation. Features include:
 .
  - Immutable package resolution with SHA-256 digest validation
  - Content-addressable local cache
  - Process-level sandboxing (cgroups, namespaces, seccomp on Linux)
  - Resource limits (CPU, memory, PIDs, file descriptors)
  - Network default-deny with manifest-controlled allowlists
  - Security policy enforcement with certification levels
  - Structured JSON audit logging
